The Scholiast's note is ‘ Luciliana urbanitate usus iu transitu amaritudinem aspergit‚’ but there is no tradition, or conjecture of value, as to the personality of the persons mentioned. 44. strabonem . . . paetum: two terms used to express different degrees of squinting: ‘paetus' expressing the lighter and one which was thought almost a beauty, so much so that it was attributed to Venus.
